Powered by RubiQube Ad Network ONITSHA – The Anambra state Police Command has arrested one Sunday Ngwu, aged 41, for allegedly beating his wife to death. The suspect who hails from Nkanu Local Government Area of Enugu State was alleged to have beaten her wife to a pulp and thereafter hit her with a metal object on the head and leaving her unconscious which led to her death. A press release issued by Mustapha Dandaura, the state’s command, Commissioner of Police said the murderer is a resident of Ikwo Street Ibollo in Idemili North LGA of Anambra State. According to the statement, police detectives attached to Awada Division got information on June 10, 2019 at about 8:pm,about the killing and he was arrested. “ The suspect allegedly beat his wife one Amara Ngwu,39 years of the same address to a pulp and then used a heavy metal object to hit her on the head leaving her unconscious.” “Scene of the incident was visited by Police detectives attached to Awada Division and the victim was rushed to Bex hospital where she was confirmed dead on arrival by a medical Doctor and her corpse was deposited at the mortuary for autopsy.” The police said. Meanwhile, the statement said the CP Dandaura has ordered for the immediate transfer of the case to the State Criminal Investigation Department Awka to conduct a discreet investigation in order to ascertain the circumstances surrounding the incident after which the suspect would be charged to court for prosecution